Enjoy large picture windows that offer views of the surrounding trees and spacious yards; each room is filled with natural daylight. Formal spaces are fantastic for entertaining family and friends for celebrations or get-togethers. Two main floor bedrooms add a great touch of convenience as well as one of them being an owner?s suite that features a remodeled bathroom with marble vanity and heated floors! Head up to the second floor to find three more bedrooms each occupying a corner of the home for maximum daylight and views of the tree canopies. A full bathroom with a double marble vanity and heated floors sits at the end of the hallway. Store your belongings with ease thanks to a walk-in closet in one of the bedrooms, and a large storage room with built in shelving just off the top of the stairs.

A recreation room, laundry room, cedar closet, ¾ bathroom, and more can be found here. The backyard is fully fenced so four-legged family members can explore worry free. Invite friends over for a barbecue and yard games in the expansive yard or sit in the shade and tend to the garden beds. The detached 2-car garage will keep cars and toys free from the elements year round. 

This home is available for pre-market showings beginning July 22nd. For more information, please reach out to Henry Edelstein at 612-270-1667 or Team@TeamEdelstein.com. We look forward to hearing from you!

description:
Recently sold: $250,000. For Sale By Owner Private showings by appointment only Monday through Friday from 8am to 2pm. Please call 612-300-3919 ask for Dawn
***Please be preapproved for financing***   Thank you!


Move in ready! Prime location! This solid built 1926 corner lot home is located in Highland Park!
Charming, well built 1,528 sq. ft. home offers 4 bedrooms, 1 bathroom and a lot of extra storage. New 25 year roof, new vinyl siding, gutters, all new windows, doors, large front porch leads to enclosed porch and entry way, large back deck , patio area and partially fenced for privacy! Outdoor security lights and security cameras, newly painted trim. Lovely landscaping with a cherry tree, a plum tree and perennials throughout! Sidewalk lined white lilac trees and a beautiful Japanese pine tree are all placed well within the landscaping!  Leveled and graded area ready for a garage! Inside this cozy home you will find beautiful all original solid wood mouldings, doors and trim and original hardwood floors on the main level! Kitchen has been updated and includes a stainless steel refrigerator and stove leading to an open floor plan dining and living room, quaint fireplace surrounded by book shelves and french doors for a possible office or study, 2 mainfloor bedrooms, bath and linen closet. Upstairs you will find new carpeting throughout with a large pine walled master bedroom with a walk in closet and 1additional bedroom, a good size closet and a bonus room to make your own also a 1/2 attic for storage. Dual zone heating upstairs(electric) and downstairs(gas). Full size basement with new plumbing and new 200 amp electrical service and breaker box, laundry area with a front load washer and gas dryer, full size freezer, new water heater, work bench area and plenty of storage space!
Located 1 block from your major highways. Easy access to MSP airport, downtown St. Paul/MPLS, Mississippi River, parks, in town shopping and The Mall of America. Close or easy commute to local colleges, Saint Catherine's, Malcalester, Saint Thomas and The University of Minnesota. Highland Park has 2 clinics close by and an easy commute to several local hospitals, Regional,  United and Children's Hospital. The states capital is only 5 miles away,  located in the Highland Park school district.
Recently sold: $590,000.

Recently sold: $385,000. Discover this wonderful Two Story classic mere steps to the river. Set on a large corner lot, this fine home has been pampered by the original owners since 1961! Step inside to find sunlit filled spaces, natural woodwork, exposed beams in the main floor Family Room, and an eat-in Kitchen. Three Bedrooms can be found on the upper level, grouped with a Full Bath, plus super storage throughout. The finished lower level is ready to be updated to an ideal Game Room, Office Nook and Craft Room. A Three-Quarter Bath can be found here, as well as a Laundry with storage shelves. Enjoy the fully fenced back yard with patio, perfect for soaking up the summer sunshine. Amazing location, just a minute walk to the Mississippi River trails, and you can bike to Highland Village for your errands. A quick commute to either downtown Minneapolis or St. Paul, the Mall of America, or the International Airport. Your cars and toys will be protected in the 2-Car gar. What a fantastic opportunity to build equity!
